docs.lead_paragraph: George Messersmith, career diplomat in the American foreign service for the last twenty-three years, returned yesterday on the United States liner Washington en route to Washington, where he will receive appointment as Assistant Secretary of the Department of State.

headline.main: MESSERSMITH BACK TO TAKE NEW POSTT; Veteran Career Diplomat on Way to Washington to Become Assistant Secretary of State

docs.lead_paragraph: The San Jose polo team arrived from Argentina yesterday aboard the Munson liner Western World and by 2 o'clock in the afternoon was settled down in its Long Island quarters at Westbury, ready for this year's attempt to win the highest honors of the American game.

headline.main: Argentine Stars, Led by Andrada, Arrive to Seek U. S. Polo Laurels; Veteran Who Helped Win Cup of Americas Last Year Will Ride With San Jose Team This Time--South American Amateur Boxers Here for Tournaments in Dallas, Chicago
